dct_description_sm: Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (GE), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , [planimetry and contours] by U. S. Geological Survey. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Franklin, Indiana : Johnson County. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3762 I NE. AMS 1. Transverse Mercator projection. A.M.S. series , V851. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, buildings, and natural features. Marginal maps: Index to boundaries -- Index to adjoining sheets. Contour interval 10 feet. "Planimetry by stereophotogrammetric (multiplex) methods by the U. S. Geological Survey 1946. Contours by plane-table methods by the U. S. Geological Survey 1946-1947. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS. Aerial photography 1944. Public Land Survey lines are based on the Second Principal Meridian and Base Line." "N3922.5-W8600/7.5." "Type C (AMS 1), 1947." "7-48." Printed with vegetation.
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army, 1948.
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); United States. Army Map Service
